{
  "narrative_prose": "I start by reading the text provided, which includes npm commands and warnings about electron_mirror and electron_builder_binaries_mirror configurations, along with glob deprecation warnings. Next, I run 'npm update glob' and receive warnings about unknown project configs and funding information. Then, I execute 'npm install glob@latest' and get warnings about deprecated glob@7.2.3 and unknown project configs, noting package changes. After that, I run 'npm fund' and see warnings about unknown project configs, displaying funding details for packages. Observing that the problem persists, I plan to check dependencies with 'npm ls glob'. I run 'npm ls glob' and receive warnings about unknown project configs, showing a dependency tree with old glob versions like 7.2.3, 8.1.0, 10.5.0, and 13.0.0. Analyzing this, I identify root causes: electron-builder and exceljs dependencies are using old glob versions, and I propose solutions such as updates, resolutions, or ignoring warnings. I proceed to run 'npm install electron-builder@latest @electron/rebuild@latest' and get warnings about unknown project configs and rimraf deprecation, with package changes noted. Then, I execute 'npm install exceljs@latest' and receive warnings about unknown project configs, with no changes. Following that, I run 'npm update electron-builder exceljs' and see warnings about unknown project configs, with no changes. I run 'npm fund' again and receive warnings about unknown project configs, displaying updated funding details. Finally, I suggest checking glob status with 'npm ls glob' to see if improvements occurred after the updates."
}

