text:
{
  "narrative_prose": "I start by running npm uninstall -g typescript and npm uninstall -g vite to remove the global packages. Next, I clean the npm cache with npm cache clean --force and verify it with npm cache verify. I check for residual config files by executing ls -la ~/.npmrc and ls -la ~/.npm/. Then, I remove WeFlow-related lines from ~/.npmrc using sed commands. I check Electron cache directories with ls commands. I edit ~/.zshrc with nano to remove alias and export lines, or use sed commands to delete them. I reload the shell configuration with source ~/.zshrc. I delete desktop shortcuts and the application wrapper with rm commands. I check for system-level residuals with find commands and kill related processes with pkill. I verify complete removal with test, npm list, and alias commands. I create a one-click removal script with cat, set permissions with chmod +x, run it with bash, and delete it with rm. I check .npmrc and the .npm/ directory, finding no .npmrc file and a normal cache folder. I return to the home directory with cd ~, stop the software with Ctrl+C, and kill processes with pkill -f electron and pkill -f vite. I delete the WeFlow directory with rm -rf ~/Documents/WeFlow and confirm with ls. I clean the npm cache with npm cache clean --force and check global electron with npm list -g electron. I check and clean .zshrc with grep and sed commands, then reload with source ~/.zshrc. I clean temporary and cache files with find and rm commands. I run final confirmation commands, showing the project folder deleted, processes detected (VS Code), and no WeFlow config. I request removal of VS Code, and the system provides steps to stop processes and delete the application and user data."
}

