{
  "narrative": "I am reading text about AI governance concepts, including the Constraint Cascade Model, Liability Paradox, and diagnostic metrics. The system is analyzing, extracting key actions and decisions: Path B regulation proposal, diagnostic metrics like Agency Index, CMI, SRD, and experimental validation stages. It is proposing Path B: Constraint-Specific Regulation with layer-specific interventions. The system is defining diagnostic metrics: Agency Index (A = D_KL × MDL^{-1}), Core Monopoly Index (CMI), Self-Referential Density (SRD). It is designing a three-stage validation methodology: Stage 1 (Monte Carlo simulation), Stage 2 (LLM inference on consumer hardware), Stage 3 (Training fork divergence on HPC cluster). The system is implementing Stage 1: Monte Carlo phase space validation with 250,000 synthetic bias-noise trajectories. It is implementing Stage 2: LLM inference using ollama with Phi-3.5-mini and Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct models across 20 temperature points. The system is implementing Stage 3: Training fork divergence analysis on HPC cluster with Llama-3.3-70B and Qwen2.5-72B models. It is computing graph-theoretic metrics: constructing semantic graph for CMI using nomic-embed-text-v1.5 and sliding attention window. The system is computing thermodynamic metrics: Agency Index via KL divergence and MDL approximation using DEFLATE algorithm. It is validating metrics through cross-correlation (r > 0.8) between Agency Index and inverse CMI. The system is formalizing Theorem 2: Dual Unmappability with proof of legal and technical unmappability, and cascade computability. It is defining a typology of constraint interactions: Override and Contamination with formal characterizations and examples. The system is proposing governance responses: architectural interventions for Override failures and contamination pathway management."
}

