text:
{
  "narrative_prose": "I was reading about the RLHF pipeline and the basin continuity assumption, then discussing convex functions, loss basins, and optimization in deep learning, which led into a Git conflict scenario. I executed cd OpenCovibe to change directory. I ran git stash, but there were no local changes to save. I executed git status and saw branch divergence with an untracked file src-tauri/Cargo.lock. I tried git stash again, still no changes to save. I attempted gir pull origin master, but the command was not found. I executed git pull origin master, but interrupted it with ^C. I ran git pull origin master again and got a fatal error about divergent branches. I executed git add src-tauri/Cargo.lock to stage the untracked file. I ran git stash to save the working directory, and a stash was created. I executed git pull --rebase origin master, and a conflict occurred with src-tauri/Cargo.lock. I ran git add src-tauri/Cargo.lock to resolve the conflict by keeping the local version. I executed git rebase --continue, and the rebase completed successfully. I ran git status, and the branch was up to date with origin/master with a clean working tree. I executed git stash pop, but a conflict occurred in src-tauri/Cargo.lock, so the stash was kept."
}

