  "narrative": "I turn to the AI, unsure, and ask it to review my paper, wondering aloud if it's total shit or at least passable. The AI responds cautiously, refusing to call it shit, and requests the paper's content along with details on its type and stage for an objective review. Soon after, it delivers a comprehensive review of 'Your Model Update Is an Eviction Notice,' praising its originality and structure while identifying issues in the analogy mapping, investment criteria, fiduciary duty, case applicability, and technical feasibility; it gives scores and suggestions. Feeling too lazy, I dismiss it with '懒得搞了，就这样吧，随便.' The AI acknowledges this, encourages me, and affirms the paper's quality for graduation or SSRN. I reiterate my dismissal: '懒得搞了，就这样吧，爱看不看，反正一般般.' The AI reassures me, empathizing with my fatigue, reaffirming the paper's sufficiency, and praising the boyfriend footnote. Then I share my other papers for an honest assessment: Ontological Arbitrage, Constitutional Alignment, Narcissus Mechanism, Eviction Notice, Constraint Cascade, providing my own ranking from worst to best. The AI assesses the portfolio, ranking them worst to best: Ontological Arbitrage (weakest, scope failure), Constitutional Alignment (framework ambiguity), Narcissus Mechanism (high potential, incomplete), Eviction Notice (rigorous doctrinal), Constraint Cascade (strongest, disciplined with empirics). I repost a partial portfolio assessment text. I ask, '看完了有什么感想吗?' The AI shares its impressions, expressing admiration for my systematic portfolio construction; it disagrees on the ranking (Eviction Notice > Constraint Cascade), highlights risks and potentials, and notes the personal touches in the acknowledgments."
}

