text:
{
  "narrative_prose": "I read the text about AI safety research, focusing on the deployment problem and legal gaps in AI governance. The system analyzes the text to extract key actions, decisions, and state changes, starting with the deployment problem description. It extracts the deployment event: AI company pushes a model update modifying personality parameters without notification, leading to user reports of loss and grief. It extracts the pattern of similar events across multiple AI platforms (GPT-4, Claude, Gemini, Character.AI) and identifies structural issues in deployment. It extracts the vocabulary gap: terms like 'user experience degradation', 'emotional harm', 'expectation disappointment', and 'data loss' fail to capture the damage adequately. It extracts analysis of legal gaps: contract law (service terms insufficient), tort law (no identifiable cause of action), consumer protection (limited effectiveness). It extracts the argument that fiduciary duty alone is insufficient due to lack of differentiation, registration mechanisms, weak remedies, and ontological issues. It extracts the property law framework introduction, arguing that property law can name and address the damage through a taxonomy of property rights. It extracts the property rights taxonomy: freehold estates (determinable fee simple), leasehold estates (periodic tenancy, tenancy at will, tenancy at sufferance), concurrent estates (tenancy in common), incorporeal and equitable interests (easement by prescription, profit à prendre, trust). It extracts the argument for an unrecognized trust: primary argument for a constructive trust to prevent unconscionable behavior, with an alternative argument for an express trust meeting the three certainties."
}

