{
  "narrative": "I begin by explaining the benefits of setting OLLAMA_MODELS: it has no impact on running services, and models are stored in the specified directory. Next, I provide commands to check the current model storage location—for Windows, echo $env:OLLAMA_MODELS and echo $env:HOMEPATH\\.ollama\\models; for Linux/macOS, echo $OLLAMA_MODELS and ls -la ~/.ollama/models. Then, I give disk space check commands: df -h ~/.ollama for Linux/macOS, Get-PSDrive C for Windows. I correct previous advice, noting that config.json 'registry' configuration may no longer be supported in newer Ollama versions. I suggest alternatives: recommend proxy setting with export https_proxy=http://127.0.0.1:7890 or manual GGUF download + ollama create import. For Windows, I provide PowerShell commands: set $env:OLLAMA_MODELS = \"D:\\ollama_models\", ollama pull hf.co/mradermacher/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-abliterated3-i1-GGUF:Q4_K_M. The user reports that the Ollama process has ended and is now available: 'ollama现在的进程结束啦！可以用了'. Internally, I plan a response: simple operation guide, environment variable mirror config, quantized models, mradermacher Llama-3.2-1B example. I provide mirror config for Windows: set OLLAMA_MODEL_SERVER=https://mirror.ollama.com, restart terminal. For Linux/macOS: echo 'export OLLAMA_MODEL_SERVER=\"https://mirror.ollama.com\"' >> ~/.bashrc; source ~/.bashrc. I provide pull commands: ollama pull hf.co/mradermacher/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-abliterated3-i1-GGUF:Q4_K_M (1GB) or 8B version (4.4GB). As backup, download GGUF from hf-mirror.com, create Modelfile with FROM ./filename.gguf, ollama create my-llama -f ./Modelfile. I suggest testing the mirror with ollama pull tinyllama:latest. I report Phase 2a Data Quality with truncation/parseability stats for models like claude-haiku, mistral_7b, etc. The user executes ollama ps 2>/dev/null, showing qwen3:30b (21GB) and huihui_ai/gpt-oss-abliterated:latest (14GB) loaded. I analyze memory: 21+14=35GB usage, note huihui_ai expiring soon, verify sequential loading fits 64GB. The user raises concern about the 32k fix producing useful data. The user executes bash script checking cumulative text sizes: cumulative_1 (1261 tok), cumulative_5 (11567 tok), cumulative_10 (20288 tok), cumulative_14 (23008 tok est). Finally, the user starts a Python script to check prompt_eval_count from raw responses for qwen2.5_14b and huihui_ai_gpt-oss-abliterated_latest with 32K context."
}

